This paper discusses the spread of false information on social media platforms, which involves analyzing social networks and text data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses the impact of false information and the algorithms developed to detect it, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of natural language processing techniques to analyze text data, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper discusses the characteristics of false information, which could also fall under the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
